Key Match Events: Donte DiVincenzo scored 26 points as the Minnesota Timberwolves defeated the San Antonio Spurs 112-110 in the NBA on Monday (December 30, 2024)
Post-Match Reflections: Rudy Gobert had 17 points and 15 rebounds for the Timberwolves, won won their third straight game
Miscellaneous Highlights: Victor Wembanyama led San Antonio with 34 points and eight rebounds
Harrison Barnes had 24 points, Devin Vassell had 22 and Chris Paul dished out 14 assists
